webpackJsonp([48671808927594],{1257:function(a,e){a.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Justin Ball",author:"Justin Ball"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/jbasdf/projects/justinball/src/posts/2006-11-08-jeff-jonas-cops-and-robbers-las-vegas-style/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:"<p>Helped track down the MIT teams in Las Vegas.\nCorporate amnesia. Ie marketing sends credit card offer to a guy in jail who just defrauded the company. Companies have multiple database systems that need to coordinate.</p>\n<p>Data and queries are the same thing. Queries persist and you ask every smart question (query) all the time.</p>\n<p>Civil liberties and privacy become a big deal. What is appropriate to ask? What if the librarian – app putting stuff in or out is corrupt?</p>\n<p>You can anonomize – if I take a grinder and a pig you get sausage but if I give you sausage and a grinder you don’t get back a pig.</p>\n<p>Sequence neutrality. No matter what order your data arrives in your result is the same.</p>",frontmatter:{title:"Jeff Jonas Cops and Robbers Las Vegas Style",date:"November 08, 2006",imageUrl:null,image:null}}},pathContext:{path:"/jeff-jonas-cops-and-robbers-las-vegas-style"}}}});
